Recipe from Spain: "IMPORTANT POTATOES"


cut potatoes into slices, dip in egg and flour and fry until golden
keep the fried ones in a pot
when you're done frying the potatoes, fry garlic in the leftover oil in the pan and add parsley and water to make a green sauce
pour the green sauce over the pot of potatoes and bring to a boil
cook until the potatoes are soft


My grandma always tells a story when she makes these: they used to be quite poor so they ate potatoes a lot. One day she had to make a nice meal to her husband father, a very picky eater. She made these and the man ate a whole pot saying this was the best fish casserole he had ever eaten JAJAJAJJAJJA
